{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic| name=Diffindo| type=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic#Spells|Spell]] (Charm)| features=Controlled destruction| appearance=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Goblet of Fire|''Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire'']]}}
== Overview ==
'''''Diffindo''''' is a destructive spell. It can be used to make seams rip and books separate from their bindings; its effects can be reversed by the [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Reparo|Reparo]] charm.
== Extended Description ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Beginner Spoiler}}
[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Harry Potter|Harry]] first uses this spell in [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Goblet of Fire|''Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire'']] to separate [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Cedric Diggory|Cedric Diggory]] from a clutch of his friends, by causing the seam on his bag to split. Cedric has to stop to collect his books, which gives Harry a chance to speak to him privately.
In [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Half-Blood Prince|''Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince'']], Harry uses this spell to keep his copy of the Half-Blood Prince's [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Potions|Potions]] book. When his own copy of the book arrives from Flourish and Blotts, Harry uses the Diffindo charm to separate the covers from the text of both his new book and the Prince's book, swaps covers, and then uses Reparo to repair both. In this way he can return a book to [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Horace Slughorn|Professor Slughorn]] that looks like the one he borrowed, but keep the incredibly useful marginal notes of the Prince.<!-- Commented out pending check in the original text: Harry also uses this spell in the deathly hallows part 1 after misteriously finding the sword of Gryffindor in the bottem of a pond. He uses the spell to brake the ice so he can dive in and retreive the sword.-->
== Analysis ==
[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Hermione Granger|Hermione]] is, of course, scandalized at any use of magic for destructive purposes; in particular, when this spell is used on a book, she is horrified.
== Questions == {{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Questions}}
== Greater Picture ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Intermediate Spoiler}}
