{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic| name=Conjunctivitus| type=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic#Spells|Spell]] (Curse)| features=Causes blindness| appearance=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Goblet of Fire|''Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire'']]}}
== Overview ==
The '''''Conjunctivitus curse''''' apparently causes temporary blindness.
== Extended Description ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Beginner Spoiler}}
In [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Goblet of Fire|''Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire'']], [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Harry Potter|Harry]] is required to get past a [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Dragon|Dragon]] in the First Task of the [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Major Events/Triwizard Tournament|Triwizard Tournament]]. Dragonhide is nearly impervious to most spells – it takes several wizards working in concert to [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Stupefy|Stun]] a dragon, for instance – so in order to disable a dragon single-handed, you must attack its only vulnerable area - its eyes. The Conjunctivitus curse is the one you use to do that.
We are told about this spell, but we do not see it actually executed, so we do not know the incantation.
