{{ingredient}}

'''Hake''' is a [[Cookbook:whitefish|whitefish]] with a moist, flaky texture and a subtle flavour, like a milder version of [[Cookbook:Cod|cod]]. It is also sometimes known as '''ling''' or '''whiting''', although in the UK, "whiting" is used to mean a different, less tasty fish.

This fish responds best to simple cooking, and can be [[Cookbook:frying|fried]] or [[Cookbook:poaching|poached]], or used in fish soup.

{{wikipedia|Hake}}

[[Category:Saltwater fish]]
